  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The removal of the stallrisers and insertion of floor-to ceiling glass panels has compromised the architectural integrity of the retained elements of the pub shopfront, to the detriment of the appearance of the building as a whole. The off-centre glass entrance door in the opening at the southern end of the frontage makes no design sense either, especially given the retention of the wooden doors serving the residential portions of the building at the opposite end of the shopfront. The proposal would harm the architectural coherence and visual amenity of the building and would hence conflict with the expectations of Policies D1, D4, D11 and D13 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002."
